# react-native-maps — build & release cheat sheet
# Notes taken for RNMaps v1.26.10+ / RN v0.81.1 (New Arch)
#
# This package is developed on both Windows and macOS.
#   - Windows can do: JS/TS work, Android, codegen for BOTH platforms, tests/lint.
#   - macOS is required for: CocoaPods (pod install) and building/running the iOS example app.

# =====================================================================
# 1. One-time setup after clone / after changing dependencies (ANY OS)
# =====================================================================
yarn bootstrap
#   = yarn --cwd example && yarn   (installs deps for example app and root)
#
# macOS ONLY — if you will build the iOS example app, use instead:
yarn bootstrap:mac
#   = bootstrap + bundle-install (Ruby gems/CocoaPods) + pod-install
#   pod-install runs: cd example/ios && RCT_NEW_ARCH_ENABLED=1 bundle exec pod install
#   (POSIX env-var syntax — will NOT run on Windows, and pods need Xcode anyway)

# =====================================================================
# 2. After changing things (before committing a new release version)
# =====================================================================
# Build TypeScript — updates dist/ and plugin/build, and makes the spec
# files discoverable by codegen:
yarn build

# Regenerate the committed codegen artifacts (ANY OS — do NOT delete
# android/src/main or ios/generated first, files are committed on purpose):
yarn codegen
#   = yarn codegen:android   -> android/src/main   (java package com.rnmaps.fabric)
#   + yarn codegen:ios       -> ios/generated      (RNMapsSpecs + delegates)
#
# These call node_modules/react-native/scripts/generate-codegen-artifacts.js
# directly with `-s library`, which is the reliable path on both OSs.
#
# NOTE on `npx react-native codegen` (the CLI variant): it also regenerates the
# app-level provider files committed in ios/generated (RCTThirdPartyComponentsProvider,
# RCTModuleProviders, RCTAppDependencyProvider, ...). Those only change when
# modules/components are added, renamed or removed. Known kink in RN 0.81: it ends with
#   [Codegen] TypeError [ERR_INVALID_ARG_TYPE]: The "from" argument must be of type string...
# AFTER generating everything except ReactCodegen.podspec — the error is harmless,
# but the process exits 1. Run it only when providers need updating, then verify
# git diff. ATTENTION: do NOT remove dir ios/generated.

# =====================================================================
# 3. Verify (this is exactly what the pre-commit hook runs, ANY OS)
# =====================================================================
yarn lint
yarn tscheck
yarn format-check
yarn test

# =====================================================================
# 4. Test the example app
# =====================================================================
# Setup example app with Google MAPS_API_KEY for both iOS and Android:
file://./docs/examples-setup.md
#
# Android (Windows or macOS): open example/android in Android Studio or
#   cd example && yarn start   +   run the app from Android Studio / gradlew
# iOS (macOS ONLY): yarn bootstrap:mac first, then open
#   example/ios/*.xcworkspace in Xcode.

# =====================================================================
# Commit hooks (husky)
# =====================================================================
# pre-commit  -> lint + tscheck + format-check + test (blocking).
#   Windows line-ending gotcha is handled: .prettierrc has "endOfLine": "auto",
#   so CRLF checkouts (git core.autocrlf=true) pass format-check.
# commit-msg  -> commitlint (conventional commits) is ADVISORY on this fork:
#   a non-conventional message prints a warning but the commit goes through,
#   so the plain "Commit" button works — no need for "Commit (No Verify)".
